Document: ScriptCreateDialog
Path: godot/classes/class_scriptcreatedialog.rst
Summary: Godot editor's popup dialog for creating new Script files.
ScriptCreateDialog inherits from ConfirmationDialog < AcceptDialog < Window < Viewport < Node < Object. Used in the Godot editor to create new Script files through a popup interface.
---CHUNK---
Document: ScriptCreateDialog  
Path: godot/classes/class_scriptcreatedialog.rst  
Summary: A dialog for creating script files using templates for specific scripting languages.  

The ScriptCreateDialog creates script files according to a given template for a given scripting language. The standard use is to configure its fields prior to calling one of the Window.popup() methods.  

GDScript:  
func _ready():  
 var dialog = ScriptCreateDialog.new();  
 dialog.config("Node", "res://new_node.gd") # For in-engine types.  
 dialog.config("\"res://base_node.gd\"", "res://derived_node.gd") # For script types.  
 dialog.popup_centered()  

C#:  
public override void _Ready()  
{  
 var dialog = new ScriptCreateDialog();  
 dialog.Config("Node", "res://NewNode.cs"); // For in-engine types.  
 dialog.Config("\"res://BaseNode.cs\"", "res://DerivedNode.cs"); // For script types.  
 dialog.PopupCentered();  
}
